To this day, it has not been scientifically proven that any drug is suitable for treating the existing infection caused by Ebola, even though there is an experimental vaccine that seems to be able to reduce the mortality caused by that disease.
Zmapp, a combination of antibodies, had a promising early field result, but formal studies showed that it was less beneficial than expected in preventing death.
In the PALM trial, the function of Zmapp was control, meaning that scientists used it as a basis and compared the other three treatments to it.
USA Gymnastics supports the statement of the United States Olympic Committee and acknowledges that it is imperative for the Olympic family to promote a safe environment for all our athletes.
We agree with the USOC statement that the interests of athletes, clubs, and their sports can be better served by making significant changes within our organization, rather than withdrawing certifications.
USA Gymnastics supports an independent investigation that can clarify how the abuse described by the survivors of Larry Nassar, with such courage, could have gone unnoticed for so long, and accepts any necessary and appropriate changes.
The goal of USA Gymnastics and USOC is the same: to ensure that gymnastics and other sports are as safe as possible so that athletes can pursue their dreams in a protected, positive, and empowered environment.
