The 802.11n standard works in both 2.4GHz and 5.0GHz frequencies.
This will make it possible for it to be compatible with previous versions of 802.11a, 802.11b, and 802.11g; as long as the base station has dual radios.
The speeds of the 802.11n standard are much higher than those achieved by its predecessors, with a maximum theoretical performance of 600 Mbps.
